	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87993><span id= >SkinnedByPavement</span></a><br><span id=notbold>185 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This weapon would somewhat be a waste in the hands of a bard...reguardless of haste effects they just can't double attack and would just do more damage with 2 different weapons.<br><br>Any tank worth his own weight in salt should be able to hold taunt over a bard, especially if they're supposed to hold taunt over classes like monks and rangers that are true damage dealers.<br><br>Bards are not damage dealers compared to warriors, monks, rouges, rangers..but they do so many good things in groups making them a damge dealer (adding double attack) would just be overpowering and unbalancing in this game.<br><br>This weapon would be far better in the hands of a SK or Pally, because for the sake of the raiding force, they will be inflicting the most damage with this thing...and they can also take the heat from aggro drawn...<br><br>And giving bards double attack would be as unbalancing as giving Pally's and SK's dual wield...SK's and Pallys aren't damage dealers either so don't feel bad bards, we're just here to tank/tag mobs...lets the warriors, monks and rouges spam the screen, but if you're playing a non ranger hybrid and expect to be a damage dealer at the higher levels you will be sorely disappointed.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Xikuliz Litecleaver<br>Revenent of Bristlebane<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107360" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107360</a><br></td></tr>
